 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3.3","title":"Square: readiness, compliance, verification, and operator guidance","description":"Finish Square with readiness and doctor outputs, merchant and permission remediation guidance, deterministic tests across payment and catalog workflows, and explicit V3 compliance evidence for a commerce connector with high-risk financial side effects.","acceptance_criteria":"- closeout requires comprehensive deterministic unit coverage for auth, timeout, retry, error-mapping, pagination or state transitions, and the highest-risk provider-specific mutations\n- closeout requires archetype-appropriate integration coverage built on shared `fcp-testkit` helpers rather than connector-local one-offs\n- closeout requires at least one replayable E2E or host-backed verification script that runs through `rch`, captures detailed structured logs, and preserves manifest, readiness, doctor, and conformance artifacts\n- operator guidance must name prerequisites, dedicated environments, redaction rules, common remediation paths, and rerun commands for the verification bundle\n- evidence attached to the bead must be sufficient for a future agent to rerun verification without reopening external planning notes","notes":"Closed after adding contract-bearing health/doctor/self_check evidence, merchant and location remediation guidance, deterministic Square integration coverage for payments and catalog workflows, a replayable scripts/e2e/square_connector_verification.sh bundle, and README/manifest truthfulness updates. Verified on the current tree with rch exec -- cargo fmt --manifest-path connectors/square/Cargo.toml --check, rch exec -- cargo check -p fcp-square --all-targets, rch exec -- cargo test -p fcp-square --test integration -- --nocapture, rch exec -- cargo test -p fcp-square -- --nocapture, and rch exec -- cargo clippy -p fcp-square --all-targets -- -D warnings.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"TopazMoose","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:21:38.409876Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-22T19:06:00Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T19:06:00Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:21:38.409876Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:21:38.409876Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.6.3.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.9.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:21:38.409876Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.7","title":"[T2-EMAIL] Tier 2 Communication: Outlook/Exchange dedicated connector","description":"Dedicated Outlook/Exchange email connector via Microsoft Graph API. While Microsoft365 connector exists, a focused email connector provides deeper mail-specific operations. Operations: outlook.messages.list/get/send/reply/forward/delete, outlook.messages.search, outlook.messages.move, outlook.folders.list/create, outlook.rules.list/create, outlook.calendar.events.list/get/create/update/delete (mirrors our Google Calendar pattern). Auth: Azure AD OAuth2 with Mail.Read/Mail.Send scopes. Network: graph.microsoft.com. REST API. Send/delete=Risky, reads=Safe. 3 subtasks.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-17T22:03:37.377606Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-18T00:25:08.728942Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.7","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-17T22:03:37.377606Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1782,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.7","author":"jemanuel","text":"Architectural note: This bead is a standalone feature under the top-level epic because it bridges the communication and productivity categories. It provides deeper email-specific operations beyond what the general Microsoft365 connector offers. Pairs with our Google Calendar connector (mirrors the pattern for Outlook Calendar events).","created_at":"2026-03-18T00:22:26Z"},{"id":1808,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.7","author":"jemanuel","text":"Testing requirements: 50+ unit tests (wiremock), 10+ integration tests (ConnectorSuite/ComplianceSuite), E2E compliance script, structured JSON logging with connector_id/operation_id/duration_ms, retry telemetry with attempt/delay_ms/error. All tests deterministic, no real API calls, no timing-based flakiness.","created_at":"2026-03-18T00:25:08Z"}]}
